## 5. Implementation Guidance

### Frontend тАУ `asset-detail.tsx`

Use the asset type name to conditionally render panels:

```tsx
const COST_ELIGIBLE_TYPES = new Set([
  'Table', 'View', 'Dataset', 'Dashboard', 'ML Model', 'Stream', 'System',
]);
const QUALITY_ELIGIBLE_TYPES = new Set([
  'Table', 'View', 'Dataset', 'ML Model',
]);
const COMMENT_ELIGIBLE_TYPES = new Set([
  'Table', 'View', 'Dataset', 'Dashboard', 'Notebook',
  'ML Model', 'API Endpoint', 'Stream',
]);
const RATING_ELIGIBLE_TYPES = new Set([
  'Dataset', 'Dashboard', 'ML Model',
]);
const LINEAGE_ELIGIBLE_TYPES = new Set([
  'Table', 'View', 'Dataset', 'ML Model', 'Stream',
]);
const IMPACT_ELIGIBLE_TYPES = new Set([
  'Policy', 'Business Term', 'Logical Entity',
]);
const OWNERSHIP_ELIGIBLE_TYPES = new Set([
  'Table', 'View', 'Dataset', 'Dashboard', 'Notebook',
  'ML Model', 'API Endpoint', 'Stream', 'Policy',
  'Business Term', 'Logical Entity', 'System',
]);
// Semantic Links are exposed on all asset-backed entities except containers
// (Catalog/Schema) and Delivery Channel. The asset detail view always renders
// the panel тАФ empty state is handled gracefully тАФ so an explicit allow-set
// is only needed if you ever decide to hide the panel for specific types.
const SEMANTIC_LINK_INELIGIBLE_TYPES = new Set([
  'Catalog', 'Schema', 'Delivery Channel',
]);
```

Then guard each panel:

```tsx
{COST_ELIGIBLE_TYPES.has(entityType) && (
  <EntityCostsPanel entityId={assetId} entityType="asset" />
)}
```

### Backend тАУ Pydantic models

Update `entity_type` validators to accept the expanded set where appropriate.
For example, `CostItemBase.entity_type` currently only allows
`data_domain|data_product|data_contract` тАФ extend it to include `asset` when
the cost tracking is expanded.

### Adding a New Entity or Asset Type

1. Add the type to the ontology (`ontos-ontology.ttl`) or as a dedicated model.
2. **Update this matrix** with Y/тАФ/╬г for every panel row.
3. If asset-backed, add the type name to the appropriate `*_ELIGIBLE_TYPES` sets
   in `asset-detail.tsx`.
4. If dedicated, wire panels in the new detail view according to the matrix.
5. Update backend Pydantic validators if the type needs to be accepted by
   polymorphic routes (costs, comments, etc.).
